<item>
            <title>[MATH-835] Fraction percentageValue rare overflow</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-835</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The percentageValue() method of the Fraction class works by first multiplying the Fraction by 100, then converting the Fraction to a double. This causes overflows when the numerator is greater than Integer.MAX_VALUE/100, even when the value of the fraction is far below this value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch changes the method to first convert to a double value, and then multiply this value by 100 - the result should be the same, but with less overflows. An addition to the test for the method that covers this bug is also included.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
